        "title": "fix: use target default branch in repair plans",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Preserve target repository default branches in repair planning instead of hard-coding `main`.\n- Preserve `target_branch` through repair comment-router dispatch and the `sweep.yml` `workflow_dispatch` fallback.\n- Removed the manual `apply_min_age_minutes` workflow input so adding `target_branch` stays under GitHub's workflow_dispatch input limit.\n\n## Review follow-up\n- The latest change closes the remaining review gap where manual `sweep.yml` fallback could still use `main`.\n- Added regression coverage for the `sweep.yml` fallback and kept the existing workflow input-count guard green.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm run format && pnpm run build:repair && node --test test/repair/comment-router-config.test.ts test/repair/workflow-sparse-checkout.test.ts test/repair/plan-cluster.test.ts test/repair/run-worker.test.ts`\n- `pnpm run format && pnpm run build:repair && node --test test/repair/comment-router-config.test.ts test/repair/workflow-sparse-checkout.test.ts test/repair/plan-cluster.test.ts test/repair/run-worker.test.ts test/clawsweeper.test.ts --test-name-pattern 'workflow_dispatch input count|sweep workflow preserves|review continuations'`\n- `pnpm run check` (passed: active surface, limits, build, lint, unit, repair, coverage, format)\n",
